!front: What kind of a field does a **Vector-Valued Function of Several Variables** define?
!back: A **Vector-Valued Function of Several Variables** \( \mathbf{F} : D \sube \mathbb{R}^m \to \mathbb{R}^n \) defines a **Vector Field**.
!related:
Function of Several Variables: \( \mathbf{r} : D \sube \mathbb{R}^n \to \mathbb{R} \)

